Alias records in Azure DNS allow mapping a domain name directly to Azure resources such as:

* Public IP addresses
* Azure App Services
* Traffic Manager profiles

Unlike traditional DNS records, alias records automatically update when the target resource changes.

For example, an alias record can point a domain to a load balancer.

A real-life use case is dynamic cloud environments where resources frequently change.

Another example is simplifying DNS management for scalable applications.

Alias records provide flexibility and automation in DNS management.
